West 64th Street, at, adjoining and east of the N. E. corner of Amsterdam Avenue (left), showing a garage at No. 167, and the Centro Galicia at No. 153-59. The latter replaced the brownstones that housed the Society of Professional Auto Engineers in 1922. View 2 shows the roof atop the garage that adjoins this building. The photographer is viewing northwestward towards Amsterdam Avenue from a point in the center of the block.
